This sit-down cafe and theater sells wine for the 21+ set, and features pretty incredible improv jazz, electronic and experimental music, and all sorts of other stuff. Check out the music calendar.Acadia Cafe\'s MySpace profile.

properties.name: Blue Nile
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  2027 East Franklin Ave., Minneapolis, MN612.338.3000. SOMETIMES 18+African-owned, internationally-populated West Bank restaurant and club features 18+ Tuesday poetry and hip-hop nights, but call for details.Check out the >a href="http://www.bluenilempls.com/livemusiccalendar.html">music calendar.

properties.name: Bryant-Lake Bowl
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  810 W Lake St, Minneapolis, MN612.825.3737.All shows at this hep Lake St. bowling alley/theater/restaurant/wine bar with cabaret seating are all-ages, including hip-hop and rock gigs. (Bring your own ear plugs.)

properties.name: Camel Club (St. Paul)
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  862 White Bear Ave., St. Paul, MN651.731.9899.A 21+ alcohol-free venue that has begun hosting the occasional 18+ and all-ages shows. I haven\'t been there, so call for more details.

properties.name: Casablanca Coffee and Tea (Blaine)
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic   12517 Central Av NE, Blaine, MN763.754.6210.This hand-painted coffee house space in Blaine features acoustic bands

properties.name: Club 3 Degrees (Minneapolis)
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  113 North 5th Street, Minneapolis, MNIn 2003, this Christian music mecca (you\'ll pardon the phrase) relocated from Central Avenue to the den of sin--the Minneapolis Warehouse District, across from the Quest--and changed its name from the New Union to Club 3 Degrees. The new holds 1,7000 people over three floors, and the lineup remains characteristically diverse: hip hop, metal, national, local, gospel.All ages welcome until 11:00 p.m.; 14 and under must be with someone 18 or older at all times. Lounge is 16+ after 9:00 p.m. Entire club is 18+ 11:00 p.m. to close (closing times are 10:00 p.m. Wednesdays, 11:00 p.m. or midnight Thursdays, 1:00 a.m. Friday nights, 1:30 a.m. Saturday nights, 10:00 p.m. Sundays.) For safety reasons, customers under 4 feet tall must use balcony for select shows. Admission is free for children under 1 year of age.

properties.name: District 202 (Minneapolis)
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  1601 Nicollet Ave S., Minneapolis, MN612.871.5559This gay/lesbian/bisexual/transgender youth center features 21-and-under dance nights every Saturday, as well as many other music events that are all-ages and open to the public.

properties.name: Escape Ultra Lounge
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  600 Hennepin Ave S, Minneapolis, MN612.333.8855. THURSDAY 18+"18 to party, 21 to drink" on Thursdays, at this swank Minneapolis R&B club

properties.name: Fine Line Music Cafe
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic   318 1st Ave N, Minneapolis, MN612.335.8181. OCCASIONAL 18+The 18+ shows might be few here, but they\'re worth seeking out at this newly refurbished Warehouse District club, which has always featured a wide variety of national acts, and stays especially good on cutting-edge country and metal.

properties.name: First Avenue and the 7th St. Entry
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  701 First Avenue N., Minneapolis, MN612.338.8388. OFTEN ALL-AGES, 18+The greatest club in Minnesota history was among the first to offer all-ages shows in the mid-\'80s, and still books them often, though sadly, the all-ages or 18+ dance nights seem to have disappeared.

properties.name: Gay 90s
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  408 Hennepin Ave, Minneapolis, MN612.333.7755. WEDNESDAYS, THURSDAYS, SUNDAYS 18+Homophobes, please find another spot: The Gay 90s has always been cool, always been gay (despite popular belief among some), and always (well, at least for a while) been a good place for cool and tolerant straights to drop by and dance their asses off to house music and hip hop, enjoy a drag show, or take in the male entertainment. The club is still 18+ on Wednesdays, Thursdays, and Sundays, from 9:00 p.m. to close.

properties.name: Ginkgo Coffee House
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic   721 N. Snelling Avenue, St. Paul, MN651.645.2647. ALL-AGESThis St. Paul spot on Snelling near the Midway is a must-stop for fans of acoustic singer-songwriters. Many stars of the genre breeze through here before and after they become big.Check out the music calendar.

properties.name: Juxtaposition Arts
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  2007 Emerson Ave N, Minneapolis, MNThough not specifically having anything to do with music, this youth-oriented arts nonprofit is a vital link between hip-hop culture and the arts world, teaching students techniques rooted in both traditional and graffiti painting.Check out the events calendar

properties.name: Loring Pasta Bar
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  327 14th Av. SE, Minneapolis, MNLakeville Teen Corporation is a teen center set up by Lakeville featuring local bandsCheck out their MySpace profileYou have to be 21 to enjoy the more atmospheric (and comfortable) Loring Bar knockoff, the Kitty Cat Klub. But this high-ceilinged restaurant down the same block in Dinkytown features 18+ hip-hop nights and other student-friendly events, so maybe it\'s the better spot.

properties.name: Patrick's Cabaret
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  3010 Minnehaha Ave. S., Minneapolis, MN612.721.3595. ALL-AGESEvent calendar.As you might guess, this is mainly a cabaret, located not far off of East Lake St., but with plenty of high school-type events that include music as well as other performance.

properties.name: Pizza Luce
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  11 E. Superior St., Duluth, MN218.727.7400. 18+ Lots of all-ages shows.Check out the events calendar on their MySpace profile.Like Arnold\'s from Happy Days run by a bunch of tattooed punks, Luce serves great grub, hosts great 18+ rock shows in its plush interior, and is just two and a half great hours north of the Twin Cities, with carding at the door.

properties.name: Segue Cafe
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic   11271 96th Ave N, Maple Grove, MN763.424.3940 info@seguecafe.com. 763.424.3940. ALL-AGESCheck out the events calendar.Christian-oriented coffee shop/youth center, with everything from acoustic music to hard rock in the evening, mostly with young performers. Closed Sundays, natch. Check out their MySpace profile.

properties.name: Southern Theater
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic   1420 Washington Ave. S., Minneapolis, MN612.340.1725. ALL-AGES.Not a lot of music at this dance headquarters, but the stuff they do feature is often good.

properties.name: The Cabooze
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  917 Cedar Ave. S., Minneapolis, MN612.338.6425.Call to find out about age restrictions (they aren\'t on the calendar), but from my experience, hip-hop shows at this big, classic West Bank bar are 18+, with a bracelet to drink.

properties.name: The Cedar Cultural Centre (Minneapolis)
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  416 Cedar Ave S, Minneapolis, MNLike the Bryant-Lake Bowl, this is a sit-down all-ages space with beer for the 21+ crowd, and a rep for great international music, jazz, and folk.

properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic   9451 Excelsior Blvd., Hopkins, MN952-938-2204

properties.name: The Dinkytowner (Minneapolis)
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  412 1/2 14th Avenue SE., Minneapolis, MN612.362.0427.This nice Dinkytown basement club with pool tables books everything from hip hop to avant-garde noise.

properties.name: The Fallout
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  2609 Stevens Ave S, Minneapolis, MN612.462.3873 ALL-AGESLaunched in 2001, this Christian-oriented youth center-cum-art space fills the old Coffee Shock niche: It\'s sponsored by Source MN, Inc., a religious-based non-profit organization, but seems to feature plenty of secular all-ages emo/punk/metal shows that don\'t force religion onto either the bands or the audiences.

properties.name: The Garage
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  75 Civic Center Parkway, Burnsville, MN952.895.4664. ALL-AGESThis is the only nonstop all-ages club in the Twin Cities that I can find, and it\'s a great scene.

properties.name: The Key
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  303 South Water Street, Northfield, MNCool cafe with great alternative diner food in Northfield, now featuring all-ages concerts put on by the Northfield Union of Youth (though the bands aren\'t listed on the web site yet).

properties.name: The Triple Rock Social Club
properties.description: Posted by Minnesotamusic  629 Cedar Avenue, Minneapolis, MN612.333.SEXY. OFTEN ALL-AGES.Check out the events calendar, which lists age restrictions
